rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseNotes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the release notes for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: secureSoftwareAttestation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF) Version 1.1](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/secure-software-development-attestation-form).
Refers to one or more Elements that are part of an ElementCollection.
The version of the SPDX License List used in the license expression.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Any other units of energy measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityAdvisory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published security advisory (where advisory as defined per [ISO 29147:2018](https://www.iso.org/standard/72311.html)) that may affect one or more elements, e.g., vendor advisories or specific NVD entries.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mavenCentral
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Maven repository artifact. The artifact locator format, looks like `groupId:artifactId[:version]`, is defined in [Maven documentation](https://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-naming-conventions.html).
Abstract ancestor class for all vulnerability assessments

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during development phase of an element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandedLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the expanded Licensing profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: affects
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) The `from` vulnerability affects each `to` Element. The use of the `affects` type is constrained to `VexAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: analyzed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a "3rd party" SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metrics
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to metrics related to package such as OpenSSF scorecards.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOutputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build element generates each `to` Element as an output, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altWebPage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative web page.
Specifies until when the artifact can be used before its usage needs to be reassessed.
Points to a resource outside the scope of the SPDX-3.0 content that provides additional characteristics of an Element.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where only one of the elements applies.
Agent represents anything with the potential to act on a system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: firmware
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides low level control over a device's hardware

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ai
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the AI profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deployed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM provides an inventory of software that is present on a system. This may be an assembly of other SBOMs that combines analysis of configuration options, and examination of execution behavior in a (potentially simulated) deployment environment.
A license or addition that is not listed on the SPDX License List.
Records the time when a recommended action was communicated in a VEX statement to mitigate a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology
rdf:Description.dcterms:abstract: This ontology defines the terms and relationships used in the SPDX specification to describe system packages
rdf:Description.dcterms:creator: SPDX Project
rdf:Description.dcterms:title: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links a vulnerability and one or more elements designating the latter as products not affected by the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Software Composition Analysis (SCA) report.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exploitCreatedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) The `from` Vulnerability has had an exploit created against it by each `to` Agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: productMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional product metadata such as reference within organization's product catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssociatedVulnerability
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Used to associate a `from` Artifact with each `to` Vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: archive
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is an archived collection of one or more files (.tar, .zip, etc)
A property name with an associated value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: availableFrom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is available from the additional supplier described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: copiedTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has been copied to each `to` Element.
Describes a certain part of a file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: file
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single file which can be independently distributed (configuration file, statically linked binary, Kubernetes deployment, etc)
An individual human being.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: review
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when someone reviews the Element.
Specifies an AI package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: doesNotAffect
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) The `from` Vulnerability has no impact on each `to` Element. The use of the `doesNotAffect` is constrained to `VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
An SPDX Element containing an SPDX license expression string.
A string in the license expression format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mailingList
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the mailing list used by the maintainer for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: green
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Dataset can be shared within a community of peers and partners.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The software is not affected because the vulnerable component is not in the product.
Specifies the type of an annotation.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: invokedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element was invoked by the `to` Agent, during a LifecycleScopeType period (for example, a Build element that describes a build step).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: eolNotice
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the End Of Sale (EOS) and/or End Of Life (EOL) information related to a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The product is not affected because the code underlying the vulnerability is not present in the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bower
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Bower package. The package locator format, looks like `package#version`, is defined in the "install" section of [Bower API documentation](https://bower.io/docs/api/#install).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: yes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Indicates presence of the field.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed during inference time by an AI model that is being used in the AI system.
Captures the domain in which the AI package can be used.
A type of extension consisting of a list of name value pairs.
Specifies the type of the content identifier.
An SPDX version 2.X compatible verification method for software packages.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: video
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is video based, such as a collection of movie clips featuring Tom Hanks.
Provides information about the primary purpose of an Element.
Provides a NamespaceMap of prefixes and associated namespace partial URIs applicable to an SpdxDocument and independent of any specific serialization format or instance.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Makes no assertion about the field.
An assertion made in relation to one or more elements.
Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: test
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Element is a test used to verify functionality on an software element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used to store extra information about an Element which is not part of a Review (e.g. extra information provided during the creation of the Element).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 256, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: evidence
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is the evidence that a specification or requirement has been fulfilled
A mathematical algorithm that maps data of arbitrary size to a bit string.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: numeric
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists only of numeric entries.
A license exception that is listed on the SPDX Exceptions list.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha224
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 224, as defined in [RFC 3874](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3874).
Describes all the preprocessing steps applied to the training data before the model training.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 512, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: binaryArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to binary artifacts related to a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: packageUrl
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Package URL](../../../annexes/pkg-url-specification.md)
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where all elements apply.
The class that helps note down the quantity of energy consumption and the unit used for measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sensor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.
References an Element on the right-hand side of a relationship.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is related to the `from` Element where the relationship type is not described by any of the SPDX relationhip types (this relationship is directionless).

Abstract class representing a license combination consisting of one or more licenses (optionally including additional text), which may be combined according to the [SPDX license expression syntax](../../../annexes/SPDX-license-expressions.md).
Specifies the CVSS vector string for a vulnerability.
Specifies a time when a vulnerability assessment was modified
Refers to any object that stores content on a computer.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sourceArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an artifact containing the sources for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_224
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 224, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: platform
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element represents a runtime environment
A characterization of some aspect of an Element that is associated with the Element in a generalized fashion.
Property describing the start time of a build.
Describes the type of annotation.
Property that describes the digest of the build configuration file used to invoke a build.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandsTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` archive expands out as an artifact described by each `to` Element.
Records the measurement of prediction quality of the AI model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition, in SPDX templating format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasVariant
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a variant the `from` Element (`from` hasVariant `to`).
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition.
Describes the confidentiality level of the data points contained in the dataset.
Capture the scope of information about a specific relationship between elements.
Identifies the text of one or more copyright notices for a software Package, File or Snippet, if any.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through instrumenting the system running the software, to capture only components present in the system, as well as external call-outs or dynamically loaded components. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as an "Instrumented" or "Dynamic" SBOM.
Provides an unambiguous mechanism for conveying a URI fragment portion of an Element ID.
Specifies whether the License is listed as approved by the [Open Source Initiative (OSI)](https://opensource.org).
Timestamp of impact statement.
Abstract class for additional text intended to be added to a License, but which is not itself a standalone License.
Captures a standard that is being complied with.
A license that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: operatingSystem
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is an operating system

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDocumentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cwe
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Weakness Enumeration](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/common_weakness_enumeration). A reference to a source of software flaw defined within the official [CWE List](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/) that conforms to the [CWE specification](https://cwe.mitre.org/).
References the Element on the left-hand side of a relationship.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kev
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerability (KEV) Catalog

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Built-in inline controls or mitigations prevent an adversary from leveraging the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: documentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the documentation for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: text
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists of unstructured text, such as a book, Wikipedia article (without images), or transcript.
Specifies the licenseId that is preferred to be used in place of a deprecated License or LicenseAddition.
An Element an annotator has made an assertion about.
Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record the package URL string (in accordance with the Package URL specification) for a software Package.
Provides an EPSS assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 4.0 - 6.9
A mapping between prefixes and namespace partial URIs.
A container for a grouping of SPDX-3.0 content characterizing details (provenence, composition, licensing, etc.) about a product.
Provides the location of an exploit catalog.
Information about the relationship between two Elements.
Provides an SSVC assessment for a vulnerability.
Describes if a given file is a directory or non-directory kind of file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: urlScheme
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) Schemes](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/uri-schemes.xhtml). The scheme used in order to locate a resource.
A canonical, unique, immutable identifier
Specifies a vulnerability and its associated information.
A value used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.
An Individual Value for License where the SPDX data creator determines that no license is present.
A collection of Elements that have a shared context.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: patch
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element contains a set of changes to update, fix, or improve another Element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has other specific context information necessary to capture that the above set of enumerations does not handle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contains
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element contains each `to` Element.
A reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content related to an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dataset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Dataset profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: modifiedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is modified by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: simpleLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the simple Licensing profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: design
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM of intended, planned software project or product with included components (some of which may not yet exist) for a new software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is a bill of materials

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 384, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.
Class that describes a build instance of software/artifacts.
An element of hardware and/or software utilized to carry out a particular function.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directDownload
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md6
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [MD6 hash function](https://people.csail.mit.edu/rivest/pubs/RABCx08.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasPrerequisite
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a prerequisite on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Provides the location for more information regarding an external identifier.
Asbtract ancestor class for all VEX relationships

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md2
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: MD2 message-digest algorithm, as defined in [RFC 1319](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1319/).
Abstract class for the portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a license.
Defines the end of a range.
Specifies the type of an external reference.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasExample
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is an example for the `from` Element (`from` hasExample `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: buildSystem
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference build system used to create or publish the package.
Commentary on an assertion that an annotator has made.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [SoftWare Hash IDentifier](https://www.swhid.org/), persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [ISO/IEC 18670 SoftWare Hash IDentifier (SWHID) Specification V1.2](https://www.iso.org/standard/89985.html) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.
Provides the license under which the SPDX documentation of the Element can be used.
Base domain class from which all other SPDX-3.0 domain classes derive.
Provides a map of a property names to a values.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDynamicLink
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element dynamically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Provides an exploit assessment of a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: graph
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is in the form of a graph where entries are somehow related to each other through edges, such a social network of friends.
Captures a limitation of the AI software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDeclaredLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact was discovered to actually contain each `to` license, for example as detected by use of automated tooling.
Refers to any unit of content that can be associated with a distribution of software.
A distinct article or unit related to Software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amendedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is amended by each `to` Element.
Provides a CVSS version 3 assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: categorical
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data that is classified into a discrete number of categories, such as the eye color of a population of people.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: scrapingScript
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset provider is not making available the underlying data and the dataset must be reassembled, typically using the provided script for scraping the data.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: extension
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Extension profile specification
Identifies who or what created the Element.
The result of applying a hash algorithm to an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: test
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's testing phase, during development.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.
Indicates the amount of energy consumption incurred by an AI model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: privacyAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a privacy assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The affected code is not reachable through the execution of the code, including non-anticipated states of the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtimeAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a runtime analysis report for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityPolicy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to instructions for reporting newly discovered security vulnerabilities for a package.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: device
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a chipset, processor, or electronic board

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDataFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element treats each `to` Element as a data file. A data file is an artifact that stores data required or optional for the `from` Element's functionality. A data file can be a database file, an index file, a log file, an AI model file, a calibration data file, a temporary file, a backup file, and more. For AI training dataset, test dataset, test artifact, configuration data, build input data, and build output data, please consider using the more specific relationship types: `trainedOn`, `testedOn`, `hasTest`, `configures`, `hasInputs`, and `hasOutputs`, respectively. This relationship does not imply dependency.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: No assertion can be made about the completeness of the relationship.
Property that describes the time at which a build stops.
Provides an independently reproducible mechanism that permits verification of a specific Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: security
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Security profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Build profile specification
A group of people who work together in an organized way for a shared purpose.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: registration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and an email registration is required before accessing the dataset, although without an affirmative acceptance of terms.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: qualityAssessmentReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a quality assessment for a package.
Specifies a data package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a version control system related to a software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when there is a security related identifier of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: container
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a container image which can be used by a container runtime application
A collection of Elements, not necessarily with unifying context.
Property describing the session in which a build is invoked.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: manifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software manifest

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Low/no risk is posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is no support for the artifact from the supplier, consumer assumes any support obligations.
Artifact representing a serialization instance of SPDX data containing the definition of a particular Element.
Describes a relationship between one or more elements.
The name of a relevant standard that may apply to an artifact.
A buildType is a hint that is used to indicate the toolchain, platform, or infrastructure that the build was invoked on.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing this version, or any later version, of the indicated License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is metadata about the `from` Element (`from` hasMetadata `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: npm
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an npm package. The package locator format, looks like `package@version`, is defined in [npm Docs](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json).
A short description of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasInputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build has each `to` Elements as an input, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Identifies the tooling that was used during the creation of the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to related security information of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: usesTool
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element uses each `to` Element as a tool, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The third-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: underInvestigationFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) The `from` Vulnerability impact is being investigated for each `to` Element. The use of the `underInvestigationFor` type is constrained to `VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
Identifies from where or whom the Element originally came.
Provides an ExternalMap of Element identifiers.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configuration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is configuration data
Records the type of the model used in the AI software.
The relative file name of a file to be excluded from the `PackageVerificationCode`.
Describes the type of the given dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityDisclosureReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Disclosure Report (VDR) which provides the software supplier's analysis and findings describing the impact (or lack of impact) that reported vulnerabilities have on packages or products in the supplier's SBOM as defined in [NIST SP 800-161 Cybersecurity Supply Chain Risk Management Practices for Systems and Organizations](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/161/r1/final).
A class for describing the energy consumption incurred by an AI model in different stages of its lifecycle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasProvidedDependency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a dependency on each `to` Element, dependency is not in the distributed artifact, but assumed to be provided, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
A distinct article or unit within the digital domain.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDependencyManifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has manifest files that contain dependency information in each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: clear
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Dataset may be distributed freely, without restriction.
Specifies the exploit catalog type.
Gives information about the circumstances or unifying properties that Elements of the bundle have been assembled under.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: red
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data points in the dataset are highly confidential and can only be shared with named recipients.
Conveys information about how VEX status was determined.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data type is not known.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The second-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this ListedLicense or ListedLicenseException identifier was first added.
Describes methods that can be used to explain the results from the AI model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasConcludedLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact is concluded by the SPDX data creator to be governed by each `to` license.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).
